    public class LocalBackendModifyDNOperation
extends ModifyDNOperationWrapper
implements PreOperationModifyDNOperation, PostOperationModifyDNOperation, PostResponseModifyDNOperation, PostSynchronizationModifyDNOperation
    This class defines an operation used to move an entry in a local backend of the Directory Server.

      • applyRDNChanges

        protected void applyRDNChanges(java.util.List<Modification> modifications)
                        throws DirectoryException
        Updates the entry so that its attributes are changed to reflect the changes to the RDN. This also performs schema checking on the updated entry.
        Parameters:
        modifications - A list to hold the modifications made to the entry.
        Throws:
        DirectoryException - If a problem occurs that should cause the modify DN operation to fail.

      • applyPreOpModifications

                           int startPos,
                           boolean checkSchema)
                                throws DirectoryException
        Applies any modifications performed during pre-operation plugin processing. This also performs schema checking for the updated entry.
        Parameters:
        modifications - A list containing the modifications made to the entry.
        startPos - The position in the list at which the pre-operation modifications start.
        checkSchema - A boolean allowing to control if schema must be checked
        Throws:
        DirectoryException - If a problem occurs that should cause the modify DN operation to fail.
